It looks like you have your MediaPlayer instances defined inside of onCreate(). This means that if onCreate() is not called, (ie the activity resumes from being paused), onCreate won't be called and your MediaPlayer instances won't exist. Nor will your button definitions.  

Basically, anything you want to persist past the first creation of the activity, you should make a member variable.

You should also @Override onPause() so that you can call nm.stop() and / or nn.stop().

You should also call release() on both and set both to null if they are not already null.

EDIT: define your variables at the top of your activity, not in onCreate() - otherwise they won't survive past that function call:

public class CustomActivity extends Activity {

//notice how I've put the button definitions up here, so they live as long as the activity does?
final MediaPlayer clickPlayer1  
final MediaPlayer clickPlayer2
Button this;
Button next;
Button previous;

//etc etc...



}

