In terms of your second question, I would say it depends on exactly how much data you have. If it's a lot of data, you're probably better off using a database anyway for performance reasons. There are pitfalls to using the SQLite APIs, such as apostrophes in the fields (make sure you use the convenience methods query, update and insert rather than rawQuery). But I'm sure there are with XML too - I don't think there's any &quot;correct&quot; method more what you are most comfortable with - i.e. do you prefer working with databases or raw XML? If neither, and you're not planning to do major updating or querying, I would use XML, or even JSON, because of the reasons above and what Jodes alludes to.

