this is a keyword that refers to the current class instance / object in most object-oriented programming languages.

For example in Java:

class ExampleClass{

    private String name = 'Example';

    public ExampleClass(String n){
        // refer to the name property of this instance
        this.name = n;
        this.initialize();
    }

    public void initialize(){
        // do something here
    }

}


Some programming languages use variants of the this keyword, such as Me in Visual Basic and self in Python and Ruby. 

