Even though it is covariant, you cannot change the return type of the interface. This is no different from the covariance in non-Generic classes.

interface Animal
{
    Animal GetAnimal();
}

class Cat : Animal
{
   //Not ALlowed
   Cat GetAnimal()
   {
       return this;
   }

   //Allowed
   Animal GetAnimal()
   {
       return this;
   }   
}


